00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:48,360
Welcome Mentor Pancake,
Mentor Off, and Mentor Mile.

500
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:53,240
- Hello.
- Hello.

501
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:54,880
You look good.

502
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,800
Still looking handsome.

503
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:00,480
It's been a while, but welcome back, Mile.

504
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:03,440
All right, today we have someone else here

505
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:06,200
to make a major announcement
for all of us.

506
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:08,080
Please welcome Cindy.

507
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:10,480
Hello.

508
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,640
SIRINYA BISHOP
MODEL, ACTRESS, HOST, ACTIVIST

509
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:15,480
Oh, no! Cindy again.

510
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:17,640
Here we go again. What new rule is this?

511
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:24,000
I've been sent by the Master Mentor
and the producers.

512
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:28,520
One contestant has lost the right
to a spot in the Final Walk.

513
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:32,200
The show wants this resolved
once and for all.

514
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:34,440
- Before we move forward.
- All right.

515
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:36,760
- Gluf, please step forward.
- All right.

516
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:39,760
Confused. Anxious. Speechless.

517
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:42,240
Should I even continue?

518
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:44,840
We have divided opinions here.

519
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:46,360
Mentor Off believes

520
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:49,640
Gluf doesn't deserve
a spot in the Final Walk.

521
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:53,080
Because you missed a campaign.

522
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:57,040
Honestly, all of them deserve a chance.
I don't know why he can't let it go.

523
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:02,280
Mentor Pancake and Mentor Ananda
think it wasn't on purpose,

524
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:03,400
because he fell ill.

525
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:06,120
He did nothing wrong.
I don't think that's fair to him.

526
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:09,360
- So the heartless one thinks one way.
- Hey, attacking me again?

527
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:10,640
And the kind ones don't?

528
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:13,160
Anyone trying to eliminate him
might be heartless too.

529
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,240
- Oh no!
- Oh no!

530
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:15,440
Thank you, Pancake.

531
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:18,400
Sending Gluf in wasn't great.

532
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:22,480
But what happened
was just part of my game strategy.

533
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:26,280
Mentor Mile, what's your take on this?

534
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:29,160
Nobody catches chickenpox
on purpose, right?

535
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:33,840
But the fact that he called us immediately
to let the production know,

536
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,840
it showed his level of responsibility.

537
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:38,400
For a 16-year-old to call
and sort it out himself,

538
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:39,880
he handled it very maturely.

539
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:43,040
Why let someone so heartless
try to kick him off the show?

540
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,520
He wasn't wrong. Just unlucky.

541
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:46,160
I'm not heartless at all.

542
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,600
If I were heartless,
I would've eliminated him.

543
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:52,200
All right. This isn't ending anytime soon.

544
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:55,400
Mentor Pancake,
what are your thoughts on this?

545
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:59,040
I think we should give him
a chance to come back.

546
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:01,120
Fine by me. But can I get two spots?

547
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:04,440
Meaning he gets one extra spot
for the Final Walk, right?

548
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,720
Can I get an extra spot too? Make it two.

549
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:10,640
You're not here to ask for an extra spot.
You're here to decide Gluf's fate.

550
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:11,640
- Okay.
- Play fair.

551
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:13,480
You got a chance to save your team.

552
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:15,840
What about my team?
They fought tooth and nail.

553
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:20,840
Today's meeting has one agenda.
Everything else is off the table.

554
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:24,840
All right. Based on this, we clearly
aren't reaching an easy conclusion.

555
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:26,160
Excuse me for a moment.

556
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,360
This feels like a huge deal.

557
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:31,840
I didn't think missing the Final Walk
would turn into something this big.

558
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:38,040
PIYARAT KALJAREUK

559
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:40,640
- I knew it.
- Oh, wow!

560
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:43,840
Wow, Tae looks sharp today.

561
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:46,840
When he walked in,
I was like, "Here we go."

562
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:49,320
We just had a little debate, Tae.

563
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:52,600
Mentor Pancake and Mentor Mile
want to give Gluf a chance.

564
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:55,480
Mentor Off agrees, but on what condition?

565
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:58,960
- One extra Final Walk spot.
- Honestly, this shouldn't be an issue.

566
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:01,680
- You shouldn't bring it up.
- He's pulling a fast one.

567
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,680
Off is always pulling things like this.

568
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:06,280
Always playing tactics. It's typical.

569
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:10,720
Calling me a schemer isn't right.
Mile probably taught you that.

570
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:13,920
Such a sneaky move.
We were literally just talking about Gluf.

571
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,200
How did you make this
about your own team, Off?

572
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:21,760
Fair or not, we've made it this far.

573
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:24,960
Every time he goes
to the elimination room, he survives.

574
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,400
Dude has nine lives.

575
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:28,280
What amulet are you wearing?

576
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,040
Why are you invincible?

577
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:34,560
I was numb. I was speechless.
I didn't know how to act.

578
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,800
The bottom line is…

579
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:44,400
Gluf has the right to enter the selection
process and do the Final Walk.

580
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,320
If Mentor Mile chooses him.

581
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:50,040
- Hear that?
- Yes. Good for you.

582
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:51,920
All right. So that means, Gluf…

583
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:54,440
You're eligible for the Final Walk.

584
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:56,720
- Congratulations again.
- Congratulations.

585
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:58,520
That gave me so much motivation.

586
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:03,360
To fight for everyone who gave me
this chance and cheered me on.

587
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:05,480
If he ends up representing my team…

588
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:08,840
Whoever it is, I'll be happy.
I'm proud of my whole team.

589
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:11,960
All right, and that concludes
today's special ruling.

590
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:13,600
Any questions from the mentors?

591
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:15,320
- Anything else?
- No, nothing.

592
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:18,400
- Got a problem with that?
- Not at all. I accept it.

593
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:22,360
Listen, everyone on the show
just helped Gluf out.

594
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:24,920
But I only want to know one thing.

595
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,280
Will Mile help Gluf
make it to the Final Walk?

596
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:30,320
All right, let's get into
today's challenge.

597
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:33,280
Let's meet the person
presenting today's brief.

598
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:35,120
Charin Siriananchai,

599
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:38,560
Vice President of Passenger Car
Marketing, Toyota Motor Thailand.

600
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:43,880
CHARIN SIRIANANCHAI

601
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:46,240
VICE PRESIDENT, PASSENGER CAR
MARKETING, TOYOTA MOTOR THAILAND

602
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,960
Today, your challenge is

603
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:50,840
a runway fashion video.

604
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:53,000
The theme is "Drive the Runway."

605
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:56,360
I want you all
walking alongside our models.

606
00:33:56,440 --> 00:34:01,200
But today, our models aren't human.
They're cars. The ones right behind you.

607
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:03,000
We have three models today.

608
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:07,200
First is the Yaris Cross Nightshade,
right back there.

609
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:10,679
It's a special edition,
rocking all-black accents.

610
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:15,320
You can notice the metro black style,
pillars, and side mirrors.

611
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:17,960
Even the roof is also black.

612
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:21,239
This creates a sleek, two-tone look.

613
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:24,280
Paired with the Cement Grey body.

614
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,679
- It really makes the car stand out.
- Right.

615
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:29,880
And it's super striking
with the Metro Stylish front grille.

616
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:33,400
Exclusive to the Nightshade edition.

617
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:37,080
Model two is the Corolla Cross GR Sport.

618
00:34:37,159 --> 00:34:40,080
This one is sportier
and way more striking.

619
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:42,120
It has a fresh front grille design.

620
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:43,719
Sporty interior seats.

621
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:47,320
Emblazoned with the GR logo
and striking red seatbelts.

622
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:49,960
A newly tuned GR steering wheel.

623
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:53,920
Sport suspension for a confident
and thrilling drive every time.

624
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:56,159
Finally, the Toyota bZ4X.

625
00:34:56,239 --> 00:35:00,280
A fully electric SUV,
imported straight from Japan.

626
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:01,800
This car is top-tier quality.

627
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:05,520
You'll notice the front design
really highlights the front grille.

628
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:07,440
It's got a hammerhead design.

629
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:12,040
The headlights sweep across,
giving it a futuristic edge.

630
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:15,960
Incredible ride quality,
thanks to the e-TNGA platform.

631
00:35:16,040 --> 00:35:18,600
Purpose-built for EVs from the ground up.

632
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,000
Smooth at low speeds.

633
00:35:20,080 --> 00:35:23,000
And super stable when you floor it.

634
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:29,080
Inside, the bZ4X is spacious enough
to seat five comfortably.

635
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:32,360
It features a massive
14-inch center screen,

636
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:35,080
connected to Apple CarPlay
and Android Auto.

637
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:40,720
Plus all the smart driver-assist features
of a modern EV.

638
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:43,720
This is wild to me.
I've never done anything like this.

639
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,360
What are we going to do with nine cars?

640
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,840
There's only four of us.
There are too many cars.

641
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:52,080
And today, directing our fashion video…

642
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:54,520
Give it up for Tim Phansiri!

643
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:56,760
Hello!

644
00:35:57,960 --> 00:36:01,680
PHANSIRI SIRIVEJCHAPHAN
THAILAND'S LEADING FASHION PHOTOGRAPHER

645
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:05,240
Tim, what's the concept
for today's fashion video?

646
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:08,480
Today, you're putting on
a runway show alongside the cars.

647
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:12,720
We're turning this parking lot
into your runway.

648
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:17,240
You need to clearly sell
the attitude of your assigned car.

649
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:21,120
And this is the first
in the history of <i>The Face Thailand</i>.

650
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:24,280
Models sharing the runway with cars.

651
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:27,480
You must showcase
the car's interior features.

652
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:29,520
At least one feature per person.

653
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:33,520
Then, walk the runway
to show off its sleek exterior.

654
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:36,520
Each team must drive at least one car

655
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:39,160
within the designated area.

656
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:42,360
You can drive it yourselves,
or our crew can do it for you.

657
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:46,520
Each mentor gets 20 minutes to rehearse,

658
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:48,960
and 15 minutes of shared rehearsal time.

659
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,760
The challenge is "Drive the Runway."

660
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:55,880
We won the master class,
so we get to pick the order first.

661
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:57,640
Which order do you want?

662
00:36:57,720 --> 00:37:00,440
I would rather take the second team.

663
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:03,040
All right, you've earned that right.

664
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:05,680
So, pick your desired lineup.

665
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:07,360
That's honestly not very fair.

666
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:10,440
Getting more time is a huge advantage.

667
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,760
So we only get to pick the running order?

668
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:18,600
Your slot today also determines
which car you'll be shooting with.

669
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:20,440
The cars are completely randomized.

670
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:24,760
Which team do you want to go first?

671
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:27,880
- I would like to pick Team Panda.
- Okay.

672
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,880
Not surprised at all. Honestly, it's fine.

673
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:34,360
We won't have to sit around
under pressure.

674
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,560
We'll do our best and win.

675
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:39,120
That means Mentor Mile's team
is going last.

676
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:44,680
I'm happy to sit back, relax,
and brainstorm while I wait.

677
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:45,880
Thanks a lot, Rome.

678
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:48,400
I need one rep from each team
to step forward.

679
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:50,280
Grab your boards.

680
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:52,520
Let's see which car
you'll be working with.

681
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:55,680
Ready? Three, two, one. Reveal!

682
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:57,320
Oh, okay!

683
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:58,680
- Cross.
- Yaris Cross.

684
00:37:58,760 --> 00:38:00,120
- Yes.
- Yes.

685
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:04,360
This model is perfect for us.
We definitely have a shot.

686
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:06,440
We can play around with so much here.

687
00:38:06,520 --> 00:38:10,040
Going first is Team Pancake-Ananda.

688
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:13,080
You'll be shooting with the bZ4X.

689
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:16,240
Second up is Mentor Off's team.

690
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:19,480
You get the Yaris Cross Nightshade.

691
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:22,240
And finally, Mentor Mile's team!

692
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:25,560
You get the Corolla Cross GR Sport.

693
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:27,000
Everyone, go get ready.

694
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:30,960
Let's do this!

695
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:34,000
Give it 250 percent today. Go all out!

696
00:38:38,080 --> 00:38:41,360
We're on location today
at a massive studio.

697
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,920
It's pretty impressive.

698
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:45,840
We have to manage the space,
and there are cars involved.

699
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:49,880
So this is going to be
quite the challenge.

700
00:38:50,480 --> 00:38:52,360
- Hello.
- Hello, Pancake.

701
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:55,520
Let me ask straight away.
What exactly are you looking for?

702
00:38:55,600 --> 00:39:00,760
I want the contestants' walk
to reflect the car's character.

703
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:04,760
They need to blend in seamlessly
and highlight the car's best features.

704
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:07,320
Any specific features
you want us to highlight?

705
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,480
- The front has a hammerhead design.
- There?

706
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:11,720
- The front grille, the headlights.
- Right.

707
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,680
The body color contrast…

708
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:17,200
- It's striking, but still very classy.
- Right.

709
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:20,280
We want an executive look.

710
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:22,440
- But modern and energetic.
- Understood.

711
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,360
Noted.

712
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:24,400
About the lights…

713
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:27,680
- I'll let you know what we need.
- Sure.

714
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:31,520
- And the music?
- It should be upbeat, with an urban vibe.

715
00:39:31,600 --> 00:39:36,600
Think street hip-hop,
but with an executive vibe.

716
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:39,200
Could you show us the car?
Just a quick look.

717
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:40,120
- Sure.
- All right.

718
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:43,360
For a fashion video,
I think they want versatility.

719
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:47,400
We're playing businessmen,
but with a Gen Z edge.

720
00:39:47,480 --> 00:39:50,920
It's a perfect mix
that suits my boys completely.

721
00:39:52,720 --> 00:39:56,200
And we got
the Toyota Yaris Cross Nightshade.

722
00:39:56,280 --> 00:40:01,360
It totally fits our team.
It's urban, stylish, and sporty.

723
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:05,040
I can picture the blocking
and how to pose the guys.

724
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:07,000
I know exactly what vibe to go for.

725
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,840
- Start the clock.
- Okay, let's go.

726
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:11,560
Is the core focus
the runway or the fashion video?

727
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:14,240
Or should we balance both equally?

728
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:16,080
I think the true format

729
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:17,800
- is a fashion video.
- Okay.

730
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:19,880
- A blend of both.
- Okay. Blend.

731
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:24,040
For the Toyota Yaris Cross,
the features we want to highlight

732
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:26,000
are mostly on the exterior.

733
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:29,360
We're open to interior shots too, though.

734
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:32,800
You could also emphasize
its compact SUV features.

735
00:40:32,880 --> 00:40:37,360
It has great utility.
The seats fold to expand the cabin.

736
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:38,760
You can showcase all that.

737
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:41,520
Here's the big question.

738
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:43,800
What do I need to do to win?

739
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:47,880
The key is bringing out the best.

740
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,520
- In both the car and the models.
- Right.

741
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:52,200
You must reflect the car's image

742
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:54,600
- according to the brief.
- Right.

743
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:57,360
For the Toyota Yaris Cross Nightshade,

744
00:40:57,440 --> 00:41:00,120
they gave us three cars for this campaign.

745
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:02,760
So we need to maximize their potential.

746
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:07,200
We have to present the cars perfectly
without making it look too salesy.

747
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:14,920
Wow, gorgeous car.
Give me a second to check it out.

748
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:17,680
Before I asked my questions,
I took a look at the car.

749
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:19,080
It's not against the rules.

750
00:41:19,160 --> 00:41:21,880
I'm sure other teams did it too.
I really like the car.

751
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:24,880
I just wanted to get
a real feel for it first.

752
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:27,080
Let's get straight to it. First question.

753
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:30,480
What new elements of the GR Sport
do you want highlighted, Charin?

754
00:41:30,560 --> 00:41:33,360
First, the design.
The grille is exclusive to this model.

755
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:35,480
- Plus the GR logo.
- Okay. Right.

756
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:40,800
The interior has sport seats
with the GR logo on the headrests.

757
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:44,840
The GR logo on the steering wheel
reflects its superior handling.

758
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:48,560
Both the steering and the suspension
have been specially tuned by GR.

759
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:51,680
How do you define "sporty"?
How do you define that vibe?

760
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:54,080
What do you want to see in this challenge?

761
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:57,160
Energetic, responsive,
and totally under control.

762
00:41:57,240 --> 00:41:59,200
About the cars modeling alongside guys…

763
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:03,320
What's the ratio? Who gets more focus?

764
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:04,680
Or is it up to my design?

765
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:07,560
Balance the fashion video
and the runway aspects.

766
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:10,240
Are you judging
mostly on the live fashion show

767
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,120
or the final video?

768
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:14,080
It will be a mix of both.

769
00:42:14,160 --> 00:42:15,080
Last question.

770
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:18,400
If my boys win,
does the mentor get a discount on the car?

771
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:22,360
I'm confident
that our concept works perfectly.

772
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:26,560
It won't get completely changed
like it did with that dining table runway.

773
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:28,120
Hello.

774
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:29,560
- Hello.
- Hello.

775
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:30,520
Okay.

776
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:31,640
Before going on set,

777
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:34,480
we had already briefed them
on exactly who needed to do what.

778
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:36,760
I have to give them credit.
They kept their cool.

779
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:38,640
We're going to walk back deeper…

780
00:42:38,720 --> 00:42:39,960
- To shift the mood.
- Yes.

781
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:42,160
- Yes.
- Walk back a little deeper.

782
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:45,240
We were completely on the same page today.

783
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:46,960
So working together was easy.

784
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:50,840
The boys had their own creative ideas,
so I let them run with them.

785
00:42:50,920 --> 00:42:54,280
I just want them to try out
what they genuinely want to do.

786
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:57,560
As long as it fits
within the framework of our show.

787
00:42:57,640 --> 00:43:00,400
Five, four, three, two, action!

788
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:02,760
Now, Donut starts walking in.

789
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:06,160
Once he reaches this mark,
can we bring the lights up?

790
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,480
The tricky part was the cars' light cues.

791
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:10,480
For the opening, we wanted it to go,

792
00:43:10,560 --> 00:43:12,040
boom, and the lights flash on.

793
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:15,680
But for the lights to flash,
we had to start the cars at the same time.

794
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:19,600
We had to sync up
so many moving parts, fast.

795
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:25,840
This round really tested

796
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:28,320
how we manage time and talent.

797
00:43:28,400 --> 00:43:30,200
I think the judges will see it.

798
00:43:30,280 --> 00:43:34,360
The other teams are done for.
We'll set the bar way too high.

799
00:43:34,440 --> 00:43:38,680
Drivers! Can we do
the first pattern, the Y-formation?

800
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,080
If we can open with that,

801
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:41,720
it'll be creative, high impact.

802
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:43,160
The client will love it.

803
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:46,200
At the start, Tim. For the lighting…

804
00:43:46,280 --> 00:43:49,360
- A-B-C-D, three times, please.
- Got it.

805
00:43:49,440 --> 00:43:51,040
Rehearsals were a bit of a mess.

806
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:52,840
First pattern was right.

807
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:54,840
But the second pattern?
That was another story.

808
00:43:54,920 --> 00:43:58,040
Why not park in the middle?
They kept driving in circles.

809
00:43:58,120 --> 00:44:01,520
We had to show
the storyboard to the drivers first,

810
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:03,600
so they would understand
the patterns we needed.

811
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:06,160
Can I have extra time?
Oh, you stopped the clock.

812
00:44:06,240 --> 00:44:08,720
Thank you.
Wishing you abundance and prosperity.

813
00:44:08,800 --> 00:44:10,600
I'm super stressed, but that's okay.

814
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:13,240
Since they stopped the clock,
we should be fine.

815
00:44:13,320 --> 00:44:15,280
One, two, three, hit the lights!

816
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:18,920
Let's go, let's go. Oh, wow!

817
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,720
You're making me want to buy the car.

818
00:44:20,800 --> 00:44:24,680
I was totally blown away
by Off's blocking.

819
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:26,840
I know we're going to kill it.

820
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:27,880
Pop the trunk.

821
00:44:27,960 --> 00:44:29,840
Yo, what's up, man?

822
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:34,440
I won the master class,
so I'm not flopping now.

823
00:44:34,520 --> 00:44:36,680
I'm owning this episode.

824
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:38,600
Come on, guys. Follow me.

825
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:42,480
There's no Team Mile today.
We're Team Corolla Cross GR Sport.

826
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:46,120
Models and drivers gather here.
Let me brief you real quick.

827
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:48,640
I called them all over
to look at this storyboard

828
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:50,960
because we're all one team.

829
00:44:51,040 --> 00:44:53,960
We weren't just here to compete.
At least, I wasn't.

830
00:44:54,040 --> 00:44:58,480
My job was to make this show
look spectacular in the time we had.

831
00:44:58,560 --> 00:45:01,160
If you mess up the real take,
it's unforgivable.

832
00:45:01,240 --> 00:45:03,800
Mile laid out every single step for us.

833
00:45:03,880 --> 00:45:05,000
No mistakes, guys.

834
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:07,280
Gluf, get out of the car.

835
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:09,240
Keep it energetic. Pose at the front.

836
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:11,400
Now, walk over to Manyoo.

837
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,720
Walk with confidence, on the beat.
Manyoo, get ready.

838
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:16,920
The blocking was so complicated

839
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:20,320
that the mentor didn't have time
to walk me through the details.

840
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:23,400
So we had to improvise
and add our own flair.

841
00:45:29,600 --> 00:45:32,800
Leo stumbled a lot during rehearsal
because he kept doubting himself.

842
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:38,080
But with his experience, I know
he'll deliver when the cameras roll.

843
00:45:38,160 --> 00:45:40,720
Hold on, let's restart.
You guys forgot the choreography.

844
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:41,680
Cut the music.

845
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:44,840
At the beginning,
we have to build it up slowly.

846
00:45:44,920 --> 00:45:48,040
Don't build muscle memory
around a mistake. If it's wrong, restart.

847
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:50,440
Okay, pan to Peem. Buckle up.

848
00:45:51,560 --> 00:45:56,040
That seatbelt pull felt stiff.
It wasn't smooth.

849
00:45:56,120 --> 00:45:57,800
It made me look totally rushed.

850
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:59,720
Like I rushed the whole sequence.

851
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:03,560
Even the way I grabbed
the wheel was totally off.

852
00:46:03,640 --> 00:46:06,280
Rehearsal mistakes happen,
but the show must go on.

853
00:46:06,360 --> 00:46:10,400
I'm giving this campaign my all
to prove I deserve this spot.

854
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:19,400
Welcome back
to the Drive the Runway campaign!

855
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:22,680
Today, each team will be joined
by very special models,

856
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:24,560
the new Toyota cars.

857
00:46:24,640 --> 00:46:26,840
But before we kick off today's campaign,

858
00:46:26,920 --> 00:46:29,600
let me introduce our two guest judges.

859
00:46:29,680 --> 00:46:33,200
Both are multi-talented
models, actors, and singers.

860
00:46:33,280 --> 00:46:35,520
Mew Suppasit and Tul Pakorn!

861
00:46:36,440 --> 00:46:40,200
- Hello!
- Welcome!

862
00:46:40,280 --> 00:46:42,440
Our first team is geared up and ready.

863
00:46:42,520 --> 00:46:45,120
Let's bring out
the first team of the campaign,

864
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:46,480
Team Pancake-Ananda!

865
00:46:50,160 --> 00:46:53,400
Going first with a one-take long shot?

866
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:55,880
It's insane. Even pros struggle with this.

867
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:58,040
The most crucial thing
is the boys' energy.

868
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,640
Are the walkies ready in all the cars?

869
00:46:59,720 --> 00:47:01,320
Middle black car is ready.

870
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:03,440
Oh, they've got walkies.

871
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:04,920
They even brought their own.

872
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:06,200
The white car is ready.

873
00:47:06,280 --> 00:47:08,000
I have to pull out every trick.

874
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:09,760
So many moving parts.

875
00:47:09,840 --> 00:47:14,640
Camera angles, the products,
and the models. It was a lot to focus on.

876
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:15,840
The white car.

877
00:47:17,080 --> 00:47:18,320
The black car.

878
00:47:18,400 --> 00:47:19,240
The gray car.

879
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:21,280
The timing was spot on.
It was a perfect opening.

880
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:23,000
So nerve-wracking!

881
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:35,720
- Great inner energy.
- Agree.

882
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:37,480
Donut has so much charisma.

883
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:39,840
He wasn't overacting, just being himself.

884
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:41,280
Donut is hot.

885
00:47:41,360 --> 00:47:43,240
- Blond suits him.
- Very much.

886
00:47:43,320 --> 00:47:45,520
That opening was killer. Donut killed it.

887
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:49,200
His charisma really popped,
especially with that new blond hair.

888
00:47:49,280 --> 00:47:52,400
He has improved so much
since the beginning.

889
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,440
He nailed the look for this brief.

890
00:47:59,040 --> 00:48:00,640
The car window wouldn't roll down.

891
00:48:00,720 --> 00:48:02,680
Donut couldn't get the window down.

892
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:06,920
So the interior features we needed
to show off were completely missed.

893
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:08,360
The camera didn't catch him.

894
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:12,440
Either the camera missed his cue,
or he forgot to look into the camera.

895
00:48:12,520 --> 00:48:15,320
- Did it open during rehearsal?
- Yes! I'm so confused.

896
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:16,640
It was fine in rehearsal.

897
00:48:16,720 --> 00:48:19,120
When I got inside,
it was supposed to roll down.

898
00:48:19,200 --> 00:48:20,480
I was supposed to touch the screen,

899
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:22,840
and the camera would shoot
through the window.

900
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:25,680
It'd catch me using the screen,
and I'd work the camera.

901
00:48:25,760 --> 00:48:28,040
But during the actual take,
the engine was off,

902
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:29,760
and the camera had already moved
to Lincoln.

903
00:48:31,840 --> 00:48:32,840
I think we did okay.

904
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:35,960
Usually, when you do this a lot,
you stop getting nervous.

905
00:48:36,040 --> 00:48:37,080
But I still was.

906
00:48:37,160 --> 00:48:39,800
Let's go. Time to show off
the spacious interior.

907
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:44,120
The camera was at the rear,
and Lincoln turned to face it.

908
00:48:44,200 --> 00:48:45,600
Lincoln just couldn't focus.

909
00:48:45,680 --> 00:48:47,440
His eyes were darting everywhere.

910
00:48:48,120 --> 00:48:51,120
It was a live, one-take shot.

911
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:53,640
But I think we still stuck to the plan.

912
00:48:54,960 --> 00:48:56,600
You look gorgeous at the front.

913
00:48:57,120 --> 00:49:00,560
Kimhan was incredibly confident.
He delivered it perfectly.

914
00:49:00,640 --> 00:49:03,640
When he added his own flair,
it became a very memorable shot.

915
00:49:03,720 --> 00:49:07,120
His instinct for interacting
with the audience is unteachable.

916
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:09,720
If it were any other guy
besides Kimhan doing that,

917
00:49:09,800 --> 00:49:12,200
it wouldn't have looked nearly as sexy.

918
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:33,520
The movement is cool, but a bit too calm.

919
00:49:36,440 --> 00:49:37,960
This blocking is sick.

920
00:49:41,360 --> 00:49:43,960
I love the backward walk with the car.

921
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:47,080
The timing of reversing
and slowly lifting his leg,

922
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:48,280
that was gorgeous.

923
00:49:48,360 --> 00:49:49,200
Right?

924
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:52,920
This is the shot the client can use.

925
00:49:53,000 --> 00:49:55,360
For a fashion show or a fashion video.

926
00:49:57,040 --> 00:49:58,400
Guys in the car, get ready.

927
00:49:58,480 --> 00:49:59,520
Lincoln, Donut.

928
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:06,120
Donut nailed the ending.

929
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:07,560
But from afar,

930
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:10,680
Kimhan completely
and effortlessly stole the spotlight.

931
00:50:12,480 --> 00:50:16,080
Kimhan really stood out
and completely overshadowed the rest.

932
00:50:25,120 --> 00:50:27,200
How they play with the headlights is cool.

933
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:31,840
Love it. Using the lights
really made everything pop.

934
00:50:31,920 --> 00:50:33,960
I'm done stressing now.

935
00:50:37,040 --> 00:50:38,880
When I stress, I dance.

936
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:40,440
So I danced.

937
00:50:42,640 --> 00:50:44,840
I tried to think about
what they wanted to do

938
00:50:44,920 --> 00:50:46,240
to bring fresh energy.

939
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:52,240
The judges were watching so intensely.

940
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:54,200
None of them were vibing with us.

941
00:50:54,280 --> 00:50:55,960
We were dancing and hyping it up.

942
00:50:56,040 --> 00:50:57,320
Everyone was dead silent.

943
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:03,080
It was dry. Like, bone dry.

944
00:51:03,160 --> 00:51:05,200
Bring it, bring the energy!

945
00:51:06,760 --> 00:51:08,840
Vibe with each other to hype ourselves up.

946
00:51:08,920 --> 00:51:10,480
So I cranked up the energy.

947
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:14,920
The car has an executive vibe.

948
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:16,920
It required a sense of maturity.

949
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:20,000
These moves kind of clashed
with that mature vibe.

950
00:51:24,680 --> 00:51:26,160
Something fell off.

951
00:51:28,080 --> 00:51:30,440
- He didn't break character.
- He kept going.

952
00:51:33,480 --> 00:51:36,440
I noticed because the wire
was dangling behind me.

953
00:51:36,520 --> 00:51:38,280
I didn't care. I just kept going.

954
00:51:38,360 --> 00:51:41,080
I'm a pro.
I handled that crisis well today.

955
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:42,280
That was intense.

956
00:51:43,320 --> 00:51:45,400
- It really was, Tae.
- So intense.

957
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:46,880
With a massive long take like this.

958
00:51:46,960 --> 00:51:49,880
From a production standpoint,
it's incredibly hard.

959
00:51:49,960 --> 00:51:50,800
I was like this.

960
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:53,560
I wanted to bite my nails.
The suspense was killing me.

961
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:56,360
Good show.

962
00:51:56,440 --> 00:51:59,400
Very different from the first walk
or the dining table walk,

963
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:01,280
which felt a bit conservative.

964
00:52:01,360 --> 00:52:04,280
Mentor Pancake is done playing it safe.

965
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:08,240
Five, four, three, two.

966
00:52:11,840 --> 00:52:14,240
If you can keep your cool
and get the job done,

967
00:52:14,320 --> 00:52:17,240
I consider that being fully prepared.

968
00:52:21,360 --> 00:52:23,880
Honestly, I was quite terrified.

969
00:52:23,960 --> 00:52:26,000
Started and ended beautifully. Perfect.

970
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:29,800
Let's meet the second team.
Please welcome Mentor Off's team.

971
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:34,600
Team Pancake is very intimidating.

972
00:52:34,680 --> 00:52:37,040
Now, it's up to our boys
to handle the pressure.

973
00:52:37,120 --> 00:52:38,200
Come on, come on.

974
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:40,480
Once it started, my heart was pounding.

975
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:42,280
Give it energy! All right?

976
00:52:42,360 --> 00:52:44,880
I just felt the power and let it out.

977
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:46,640
Through my hands, through my face.

978
00:52:46,720 --> 00:52:47,640
Mostly here.

979
00:52:47,720 --> 00:52:50,400
Hit me with the lights and the music.

980
00:52:54,280 --> 00:52:55,600
I had fun, I enjoyed it.

981
00:52:57,480 --> 00:52:59,960
Our car is
the Toyota Yaris Cross Nightshade.

982
00:53:00,040 --> 00:53:03,480
Sporty, fun, and urban.

983
00:53:07,280 --> 00:53:09,760
The first five seconds
were literally just his butt.

984
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:14,160
In a normal fashion theme,
you need to grab attention instantly.

985
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,720
They just keep swiping things.

986
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:17,360
We wanted the car to stand out.

987
00:53:17,440 --> 00:53:20,560
But we forgot that we were facing
our backsides to the judges.

988
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:23,400
If the judges don't see it,
I'll voice it for them.

989
00:53:25,080 --> 00:53:27,520
Wow, forming a Y for Yaris.

990
00:53:27,600 --> 00:53:29,680
Hyping up your own team, huh?

991
00:53:30,240 --> 00:53:31,520
Guiding the judges already?

992
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:35,600
Followed by presenting the wheels.
Absolutely beautiful.

993
00:53:37,960 --> 00:53:39,360
I was owning the camera.

994
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:42,000
As soon as the camera panned down…

995
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:44,760
I walked over, cut in front,
and gave the car a touch.

996
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:48,320
But in the end, we absolutely loved
the Toyota Yaris Cross Nightshade.

997
00:53:54,480 --> 00:53:55,520
Bonus!

998
00:53:57,640 --> 00:53:59,240
- Yes.
- Yes.

999
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:01,840
A little magic show! A magic show!

1000
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:04,640
I'm so proud! How was that?
We nailed it, right?

1001
00:54:04,720 --> 00:54:06,200
Hey, that's wow. That's chic.

1002
00:54:06,280 --> 00:54:07,960
A little touch of magic, but cute.

1003
00:54:08,040 --> 00:54:09,840
- When did they get in?
- Good angles.

1004
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:10,960
It's all just angles.

1005
00:54:11,040 --> 00:54:13,680
I don't think the judges
even noticed that.

1006
00:54:13,760 --> 00:54:16,160
That the other two
were already in the car.

1007
00:54:16,240 --> 00:54:19,040
Pom and I had to get
into position behind the car.

1008
00:54:19,120 --> 00:54:20,840
Ready for the next scene.

1009
00:54:20,920 --> 00:54:23,400
It's spacious inside.
It fits two people comfortably.

1010
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,240
We kept it fun, upbeat, and party-like.

1011
00:54:28,320 --> 00:54:29,880
Go for it, boys. Give your all.

1012
00:54:29,960 --> 00:54:32,880
For the Yaris Cross,
we have to showcase modernity.

1013
00:54:32,960 --> 00:54:36,080
Energy, paired with youthful
coolness and fun.

1014
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:44,000
I switched the styles,
walked in with a fierce face.

1015
00:54:44,080 --> 00:54:47,280
I couldn't find the cam,
so I served face to Royal Mom instead.

1016
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:49,680
Fierce eyes, serve face, strike a pose.

1017
00:54:52,720 --> 00:54:54,360
Oh, is this a crosswalk?

1018
00:54:54,440 --> 00:54:56,520
Wow, for Yaris Cross!

1019
00:54:56,600 --> 00:54:58,680
He's constantly guiding the judges.

1020
00:54:59,280 --> 00:55:01,760
Without all that guidance,
I wouldn't have noticed.

1021
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:04,880
Well, speaking of that.
Ananda guided the judges last time.

1022
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:07,200
That turn was way too close to the model.

1023
00:55:07,280 --> 00:55:10,360
I'm confident. I've got a special talent.

1024
00:55:10,440 --> 00:55:11,840
My runway walk was fierce.

1025
00:55:15,280 --> 00:55:16,480
This part is good.

1026
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:17,480
This is good.

1027
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:19,320
Just like before, sell the car.

1028
00:55:19,400 --> 00:55:21,280
In my head, I really love that car.

1029
00:55:21,360 --> 00:55:24,720
Nice wheels. I paced back and forth,
letting my character shine.

1030
00:55:24,800 --> 00:55:25,880
Booty down, booty up.

1031
00:55:25,960 --> 00:55:29,480
- Touching it like he's about to steal it.
- Right? My thoughts too.

1032
00:55:29,560 --> 00:55:31,120
- Looks dangerous.
- Suspicious.

1033
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:35,160
- Might be the outfit and face.
- Sorry, I can change outfits, not my face.

1034
00:55:35,240 --> 00:55:36,520
Why touch the car?

1035
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:38,760
- Appreciate the color, cement grey.
- Right.

1036
00:55:38,840 --> 00:55:41,960
The way they touched the car
killed the mood. Too sluggish.

1037
00:55:42,040 --> 00:55:44,480
When he touched the gray car

1038
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:46,160
and the wheels too.

1039
00:55:46,240 --> 00:55:47,560
I think it wasn't sharp.

1040
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:51,560
Trying too hard to sell something
makes people change the channel.

1041
00:55:55,640 --> 00:55:58,840
I loved the moment
they got in and let the car shine.

1042
00:55:58,920 --> 00:56:01,720
- These cars are our models too.
- Oh, the models.

1043
00:56:01,800 --> 00:56:03,920
We showed these men,
now it's time for the cars.

1044
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:06,640
It felt a bit repetitive and dragged on.

1045
00:56:06,720 --> 00:56:08,960
It needed a real climax before the end.

1046
00:56:09,040 --> 00:56:12,920
It might feel a bit quiet
and lack the impact of the others.

1047
00:56:13,000 --> 00:56:14,720
But we felt it was super smooth.

1048
00:56:17,280 --> 00:56:20,280
He stepped out looking like a new man.
Where did his old clothes go?

1049
00:56:20,360 --> 00:56:23,600
I was quietly panicking in the car,
then stepped out feeling brand new.

1050
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:25,720
- Oh, wow.
- Yes.

1051
00:56:25,800 --> 00:56:27,080
That was a quick change.

1052
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:30,240
The new outfit should've had
a totally different vibe

1053
00:56:30,320 --> 00:56:31,480
from the original look.

1054
00:56:31,560 --> 00:56:34,640
Honestly, I didn't notice it,
but the narration sold it.

1055
00:56:34,720 --> 00:56:37,840
I have to praise Off.
He played the game perfectly on set.

1056
00:56:37,920 --> 00:56:41,880
My job was to get my boys
to the finish line. That's all.

1057
00:56:41,960 --> 00:56:44,960
Now I get why boxing matches
have commentators.

1058
00:56:45,760 --> 00:56:47,680
The music totally changed the mood.

1059
00:56:48,320 --> 00:56:51,880
It fell a bit flat right at the end.
It hurt the mood a little.

1060
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:55,440
We're in the final episodes now.
I want us all to make it to the end.

1061
00:56:56,160 --> 00:56:59,920
Winning is another story. We'll see.
But overall, I'm happy.

1062
00:57:02,200 --> 00:57:04,760
I think everything
came together perfectly.

1063
00:57:04,840 --> 00:57:07,360
We just kept it cool
and ended with some handsome poses.

1064
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:09,800
- The formation is stunning.
- Right.

1065
00:57:09,880 --> 00:57:10,960
A stunning ending.

1066
00:57:11,040 --> 00:57:13,680
I'm glad we gave them that energy.

1067
00:57:13,760 --> 00:57:16,280
All of them matched that energy perfectly.

1068
00:57:16,360 --> 00:57:18,560
I loved working on this.

1069
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:20,080
That's a wrap.

1070
00:57:25,760 --> 00:57:27,800
They knew they had nailed it.

1071
00:57:27,880 --> 00:57:30,640
And they were glowing
as they walked off set.

1072
00:57:30,720 --> 00:57:32,520
They gave it their all and owned it.

1073
00:57:32,600 --> 00:57:36,400
Tough choice for the client and judges.

1074
00:57:36,480 --> 00:57:38,360
Because it was so fun to watch.

1075
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:39,840
Give us a nice bow.

1076
00:57:39,920 --> 00:57:40,840
Okay.

1077
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:43,880
- Do they look like car thieves?
- Yes.

1078
00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:45,080
- Still?
- Yes.

1079
00:57:45,160 --> 00:57:46,520
Hey, did you get the keys?

1080
00:57:46,600 --> 00:57:49,480
Judges, please have mercy
on these car thieves.

1081
00:57:49,560 --> 00:57:52,000
No stealing, just nailing the brief.
Thank you.

1082
00:57:57,920 --> 00:58:01,160
And now, the final team
for the Drive the Runway campaign.

1083
00:58:01,240 --> 00:58:03,040
Team Mentor Mile, come on out!

1084
00:58:04,360 --> 00:58:05,840
Come on!

1085
00:58:05,920 --> 00:58:06,840
Come on!

1086
00:58:08,320 --> 00:58:10,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

1087
00:58:10,480 --> 00:58:11,840
All right, let's go. Go!

1088
00:58:14,720 --> 00:58:15,720
They're energetic.

1089
00:58:15,800 --> 00:58:20,120
I'm pretty confident in our plan.
It's stunning and totally unique.

1090
00:58:28,560 --> 00:58:31,080
Here we go. The show must go on.

1091
00:58:31,160 --> 00:58:33,360
Beat drop, lights on.
Next beat, lights on.

1092
00:58:33,440 --> 00:58:35,800
Fourth beat, lights on,
and cue the upbeat.

1093
00:58:35,880 --> 00:58:37,400
I mapped it to the music.

1094
00:58:40,480 --> 00:58:42,320
It is my favorite track of the three.

1095
00:58:42,400 --> 00:58:45,760
If this were a real commercial,
these beats are everything.

1096
00:58:48,800 --> 00:58:51,080
Gluf! Gluf!

1097
00:58:51,160 --> 00:58:53,240
Gluf hit the beat and passed it to Manyoo.

1098
00:58:53,320 --> 00:58:54,960
They looked confident. I'm happy.

1099
00:58:55,040 --> 00:58:56,680
We want to represent the brand.

1100
00:58:56,760 --> 00:59:01,280
Like, "These are our cars,
and we love them."

1101
00:59:03,600 --> 00:59:06,280
- That's good.
- They transition between characters well.

1102
00:59:06,360 --> 00:59:09,560
Team Mentor Mile's opening
gave me chills. It was intimidating.

1103
00:59:09,640 --> 00:59:14,000
I loved their transitions and pacing.
Everyone worked the camera perfectly.

1104
00:59:15,080 --> 00:59:16,920
They're presenting the product.

1105
00:59:17,000 --> 00:59:19,480
Selling the car without trying too hard.

1106
00:59:19,560 --> 00:59:21,600
Everything fell right into place.

1107
00:59:23,400 --> 00:59:24,400
Yes!

1108
00:59:24,480 --> 00:59:26,360
- Let's go.
- Is that the real honk?

1109
00:59:26,440 --> 00:59:28,920
Yes, it was to signal the next move.

1110
00:59:29,000 --> 00:59:33,080
Beep-beep! Off loved it, Pan loved it.
Everyone was thrilled, then we drove off.

1111
00:59:36,320 --> 00:59:38,080
It was sporty and active.

1112
00:59:38,160 --> 00:59:40,840
The transitions between the car
and the models

1113
00:59:40,920 --> 00:59:42,480
felt powerful.

1114
00:59:44,280 --> 00:59:47,000
Stunning. It made me want
to jump in that car too.

1115
00:59:47,080 --> 00:59:49,560
The lighting hit
at the exact right moment.

1116
00:59:49,640 --> 00:59:50,960
This is the winning shot.

1117
00:59:51,960 --> 00:59:54,080
They're crossing too. Crossing paths.

1118
00:59:54,160 --> 00:59:55,040
- Okay!
- Yes!

1119
00:59:55,120 --> 00:59:57,400
- Okay!
- Cross GR Sport.

1120
00:59:58,680 --> 01:00:00,640
The first part was a nine out of ten.

1121
01:00:02,120 --> 01:00:05,640
With so little time and such a huge crew,
perfection is impossible.

1122
01:00:05,720 --> 01:00:08,520
This is the Corolla Cross GR Sport.

1123
01:00:08,600 --> 01:00:10,320
It gives off an active vibe,

1124
01:00:10,400 --> 01:00:13,280
and the energy totally matches
what this car is all about.

1125
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:20,160
- Oh, boy. That was so close.
- Oh, no!

1126
01:00:25,400 --> 01:00:27,720
Is the car going to bump into Leo?

1127
01:00:27,800 --> 01:00:29,880
Leo totally lost his composure too.

1128
01:00:29,960 --> 01:00:32,800
That little jolt really threw me off.

1129
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:35,200
Peem looked so panicked on camera.

1130
01:00:35,280 --> 01:00:37,920
Peem hesitated, unsure how to help Leo.

1131
01:00:38,000 --> 01:00:39,840
So the whole thing started to fall apart.

1132
01:00:41,080 --> 01:00:43,680
- What just happened?
- Why did he drive over there?

1133
01:00:44,520 --> 01:00:47,200
- Did the driver miss his cue?
- Formation seems right.

1134
01:00:47,280 --> 01:00:49,480
The driver parked incorrectly.
What do we do now?

1135
01:00:50,560 --> 01:00:53,040
Wait, the car formation is completely off.

1136
01:00:55,520 --> 01:00:56,880
I was confused too.

1137
01:00:56,960 --> 01:00:59,400
No idea what they were trying
to showcase there.

1138
01:00:59,480 --> 01:01:00,720
That was wrong.

1139
01:01:00,800 --> 01:01:04,320
We rehearsed a crosswalk from both sides.

1140
01:01:04,400 --> 01:01:06,720
Looping back to hit the mark.

1141
01:01:06,800 --> 01:01:08,320
Reset. This part is crucial.

1142
01:01:08,400 --> 01:01:10,560
Manyoo, get out now, hurry!

1143
01:01:10,640 --> 01:01:12,760
Make it quick and energetic!

1144
01:01:12,840 --> 01:01:14,520
Energy, guys! Give me more energy!

1145
01:01:14,600 --> 01:01:16,400
Leo's walk was relaxed.

1146
01:01:16,480 --> 01:01:18,320
It wasn't working.

1147
01:01:18,960 --> 01:01:20,120
Oh, right.

1148
01:01:20,200 --> 01:01:22,000
That dead air lasted way too long.

1149
01:01:22,080 --> 01:01:24,040
We froze and stood there quite a while.

1150
01:01:24,120 --> 01:01:25,920
Leo and I completely lost our smiles.

1151
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:27,280
Oh, boy.

1152
01:01:28,240 --> 01:01:29,360
That was bad.

1153
01:01:29,440 --> 01:01:32,040
I mean, I'm not mad, but…

1154
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:35,200
If this were my gig
and we weren't filming live,

1155
01:01:35,280 --> 01:01:36,800
I would cuss them out.

1156
01:01:36,880 --> 01:01:38,960
I'm not joking.

1157
01:01:39,040 --> 01:01:41,640
But it's their first time.
I'll let it slide.

1158
01:01:42,960 --> 01:01:46,400
I just tried to keep it smooth
and tried to reconnect.

1159
01:01:51,360 --> 01:01:54,520
The second that door opened,
we got to own it.

1160
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:58,280
Compared to how I used to be,
I think I did quite well.

1161
01:02:03,480 --> 01:02:04,920
What is Leo saying?

1162
01:02:05,000 --> 01:02:07,600
They're giving a flashmob vibe, right?
A bit cringey.

1163
01:02:07,680 --> 01:02:09,960
Leo's energy was insane.
He pushed through.

1164
01:02:10,040 --> 01:02:11,200
Leo kept the hype alive.

1165
01:02:17,240 --> 01:02:19,160
What was that? What's with the megaphone?

1166
01:02:19,240 --> 01:02:20,320
I'm so confused.

1167
01:02:20,400 --> 01:02:22,200
What were you even yelling?

1168
01:02:22,280 --> 01:02:26,000
You could see his confidence drop.
It totally killed his charisma.

1169
01:02:26,080 --> 01:02:28,000
Unlike the opening. Everything felt off.

1170
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:29,600
It's like looking in a mirror.

1171
01:02:29,680 --> 01:02:32,720
I love this storytelling.
The taste level is completely there.

1172
01:02:32,800 --> 01:02:35,120
We needed something fresh for the show.

1173
01:02:37,160 --> 01:02:40,960
In the second half, we gave them space
to let their true personalities shine.

1174
01:02:41,040 --> 01:02:44,680
This stage should be
their playground to get creative.

1175
01:02:46,160 --> 01:02:48,800
Totally matched the car
with our characters.

1176
01:02:48,880 --> 01:02:52,800
Honestly, I've never given
a perfect performance.

1177
01:02:52,880 --> 01:02:55,600
But this time,
I would say I hit a solid 85.

1178
01:02:59,440 --> 01:03:02,000
- Nice.
- Wow, how did he hold that pose?

1179
01:03:02,080 --> 01:03:05,720
The ending was solid for me.
Everyone looked incredibly sharp.

1180
01:03:05,800 --> 01:03:09,320
It's hard to replicate rehearsal.
I was less nervous doing it live.

1181
01:03:09,400 --> 01:03:12,760
We already won.
We're definitely partying after this.

1182
01:03:14,560 --> 01:03:17,080
Okay.

1183
01:03:19,720 --> 01:03:23,520
Can I send the driver to the Black Room?
He totally messed up the formation.

1184
01:03:23,600 --> 01:03:24,440
Oh, no.

1185
01:03:24,520 --> 01:03:26,400
I wanted the cars to park perfectly.

1186
01:03:26,480 --> 01:03:30,120
To give the vibe that they're exploring
a new place together.

1187
01:03:30,200 --> 01:03:33,840
Honestly, I'm really rooting
for Team Mile.

1188
01:03:33,920 --> 01:03:38,440
Let me process exactly
what just happened out there.

1189
01:03:38,520 --> 01:03:41,600
I need to take a closer look
at that replay.

1190
01:03:41,680 --> 01:03:42,680
Got it.

1191
01:03:42,760 --> 01:03:45,080
What should I do?

1192
01:03:45,160 --> 01:03:47,080
Who should I send to the Black Room?

1193
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:50,160
And now, we have one final show left.

1194
01:03:50,240 --> 01:03:53,160
If you're ready,
let's kick off the finale show!

1195
01:03:56,520 --> 01:04:01,120
It's week six, guys!
Show absolutely everything on the runway!

1196
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:05,120
It's time to show us
what you're truly capable of.

1197
01:04:11,120 --> 01:04:13,520
Wow, the cars are so sick!

1198
01:04:14,840 --> 01:04:18,280
Whatever happens out there,
it's live, so own it with confidence.

1199
01:04:18,360 --> 01:04:19,920
Stay present in the moment.

1200
01:04:26,600 --> 01:04:28,040
- That woke me up!
- Woke me up!

1201
01:04:28,560 --> 01:04:29,800
- Right?
- Yes.

1202
01:04:29,880 --> 01:04:34,840
The honking and the high beams,
it just spiked the energy.

1203
01:04:37,080 --> 01:04:38,480
So hot!

1204
01:04:44,800 --> 01:04:46,120
That was good.

1205
01:04:49,200 --> 01:04:50,560
Altogether, impactful.

1206
01:04:50,640 --> 01:04:52,480
- They look great.
- Yes.

1207
01:04:52,560 --> 01:04:55,200
Each team served
a completely different vibe.

1208
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:56,320
And that was good.

1209
01:05:07,680 --> 01:05:10,520
- And that concludes our finale runway!
- Okay.

1210
01:05:11,120 --> 01:05:14,280
They pulled it off well,
ten models and nine cars.

1211
01:05:14,360 --> 01:05:17,160
The crew really put their hearts
into this for our boys.

1212
01:05:17,760 --> 01:05:21,040
Now, let's hear
what the judges have to say.

1213
01:05:21,120 --> 01:05:26,200
This fashion video is the final product
that should be ready for the client.

1214
01:05:26,280 --> 01:05:27,800
We're going to find which team

1215
01:05:27,880 --> 01:05:30,680
delivered the smoothest run
with the fewest flaws.

1216
01:05:30,760 --> 01:05:33,720
Let's start with Mentor Pancake
and Ananda's team.

1217
01:05:33,800 --> 01:05:37,600
For Mentor Pancake and Ananda's team,
presenting the bZ4X…

1218
01:05:37,680 --> 01:05:40,400
It had a very calm yet powerful vibe.

1219
01:05:40,480 --> 01:05:44,400
Today's performance
was absolutely excellent.

1220
01:05:44,480 --> 01:05:48,400
Especially the movement.
The guys and the cars synced up perfectly.

1221
01:05:48,480 --> 01:05:51,680
The way you used the lights and the cars…

1222
01:05:51,760 --> 01:05:55,120
It elevated the performance,
making it super fun and thrilling.

1223
01:05:55,200 --> 01:05:57,720
- That's what I loved about it.
- Thank you.

1224
01:05:57,800 --> 01:06:03,560
It was a fantastic opening show
that really grabbed my attention.

1225
01:06:04,200 --> 01:06:07,640
Right from the moment
they walked down the stairs.

1226
01:06:07,720 --> 01:06:10,480
What really stuck with me was…

1227
01:06:10,560 --> 01:06:14,320
when Kimhan stepped back,
and the car followed, it was…

1228
01:06:14,400 --> 01:06:15,800
Wow, just amazing.

1229
01:06:15,880 --> 01:06:17,280
There were flaws, though.

1230
01:06:17,360 --> 01:06:20,760
The shot where we were supposed
to see inside the car…

1231
01:06:20,840 --> 01:06:24,440
That feature was totally lost.
Such a missed opportunity.

1232
01:06:24,520 --> 01:06:27,200
Donut has that raw, rugged energy.

1233
01:06:27,280 --> 01:06:29,680
So when it came to cars and machines,

1234
01:06:29,760 --> 01:06:31,360
he was totally in his element.

1235
01:06:31,440 --> 01:06:33,320
As for Lincoln, I have to say…

1236
01:06:33,400 --> 01:06:35,120
You need to be ready.

1237
01:06:35,200 --> 01:06:38,760
Sometimes his eyes go blank,
or he just lacks…

1238
01:06:38,840 --> 01:06:40,880
that sharpness the other guys have.

1239
01:06:40,960 --> 01:06:43,000
Pan's show really surprised me.

1240
01:06:43,080 --> 01:06:46,040
I could see Pan throw playing it safe
right out the window.

1241
01:06:46,120 --> 01:06:50,480
You stepped out of the box
and made it super fun to watch.

1242
01:06:50,560 --> 01:06:54,400
I'm just glad our whole team
managed to create something totally new.

1243
01:06:54,480 --> 01:06:57,640
Let's move on
to our second team, Mentor Off's.

1244
01:06:57,720 --> 01:07:01,880
The Yaris Cross
is a city car built for fun.

1245
01:07:01,960 --> 01:07:05,720
You presented both the cars
and the models so seamlessly.

1246
01:07:05,800 --> 01:07:07,400
It was a really fun show.

1247
01:07:07,480 --> 01:07:08,800
All the choreography,

1248
01:07:08,880 --> 01:07:11,840
it felt like it had a hidden meaning
to sell the car.

1249
01:07:11,920 --> 01:07:14,280
It's tough. It's neck-and-neck
with Pan's team.

1250
01:07:14,360 --> 01:07:18,640
Looking at all three teams overall,
Off played it the safest.

1251
01:07:19,360 --> 01:07:22,720
But doing that meant the guys
didn't have to carry a massive burden.

1252
01:07:22,800 --> 01:07:25,800
They looked cohesive,
with no one outshining the rest.

1253
01:07:25,880 --> 01:07:27,840
It was highly entertaining.

1254
01:07:27,920 --> 01:07:31,120
But I had an issue with the opening.
I saw their butts.

1255
01:07:31,200 --> 01:07:35,560
You should've drawn us
into the story a lot faster.

1256
01:07:35,640 --> 01:07:38,400
Overall, it dragged on a bit.

1257
01:07:38,480 --> 01:07:40,240
There were some surprising moments.

1258
01:07:40,320 --> 01:07:42,480
Touching the car totally killed the vibe.

1259
01:07:42,560 --> 01:07:46,400
Then came the outfit change later on,
which finally brought the energy back.

1260
01:07:46,480 --> 01:07:50,040
If Off hadn't narrated every single shot,

1261
01:07:50,120 --> 01:07:51,920
I'm not sure we would've known
what's going on.

1262
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:55,120
Honestly, without the narration,
it would've been so flat.

1263
01:07:55,200 --> 01:07:58,480
Bonus is a very niche kind of handsome.

1264
01:07:58,560 --> 01:08:00,840
Rome and Pom are straight-up models.

1265
01:08:00,920 --> 01:08:04,680
But today, Bonus blended in perfectly
with Rome and Pom.

1266
01:08:04,760 --> 01:08:06,040
I really loved that.

1267
01:08:06,120 --> 01:08:09,200
All right, we've heard
the feedback for two teams.

1268
01:08:09,280 --> 01:08:11,720
Now for our final team,
Mentor Mile's team.

1269
01:08:11,800 --> 01:08:16,279
Yes, Mile's team represented
the Corolla Cross GR Sport.

1270
01:08:16,359 --> 01:08:18,840
I really want to praise that opening.

1271
01:08:18,920 --> 01:08:21,720
I could really feel the confidence.

1272
01:08:21,800 --> 01:08:24,720
The runway walk syncing
with the beat made it super fun.

1273
01:08:24,800 --> 01:08:25,960
The energy was felt.

1274
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:30,960
However, the middle section
was completely disconnected.

1275
01:08:31,040 --> 01:08:33,279
They definitely stumbled a bit.

1276
01:08:34,279 --> 01:08:37,080
I really admire Mile's concept.

1277
01:08:37,160 --> 01:08:39,720
The storyline was crystal clear.

1278
01:08:39,800 --> 01:08:42,200
And the transitions
were incredibly smooth.

1279
01:08:42,279 --> 01:08:45,760
There was one shot that made
all of us go, "Wow."

1280
01:08:45,840 --> 01:08:50,479
Even if the middle section
got a little confusing,

1281
01:08:50,560 --> 01:08:55,000
it was just an ambitious
technical challenge.

1282
01:08:55,080 --> 01:08:56,920
Which killed the momentum slightly.

1283
01:08:57,000 --> 01:08:58,840
I agree with Cindy's feedback.

1284
01:08:58,920 --> 01:09:02,760
She caught every detail and didn't
hold back, be it praise or critique.

1285
01:09:02,840 --> 01:09:06,120
Mile's show looked incredibly strong.

1286
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:09,279
And it was risky to have four models.

1287
01:09:09,359 --> 01:09:11,680
There were so many elements.

1288
01:09:11,760 --> 01:09:15,279
With all those cars and people,
it was very hard to pull off.

1289
01:09:15,359 --> 01:09:17,120
And they didn't handle it smoothly.

1290
01:09:17,200 --> 01:09:21,520
Manyoo looked incredibly handsome
and performed naturally today.

1291
01:09:21,600 --> 01:09:24,040
Peem was still a bit awkward, though.

1292
01:09:24,120 --> 01:09:28,800
But it's endearing. Hit or miss,
Peem always gives it his all.

1293
01:09:28,880 --> 01:09:32,760
I didn't expect much from Leo,
coming in with his rapper vibe.

1294
01:09:32,840 --> 01:09:34,600
But he was actually charming.

1295
01:09:34,680 --> 01:09:38,080
And Gluf really tried to project strength.

1296
01:09:38,160 --> 01:09:42,479
By the middle, it just fell apart.
Let's not kid ourselves.

1297
01:09:42,560 --> 01:09:46,359
I was really rooting for Mile today.

1298
01:09:46,439 --> 01:09:51,000
Even though
he probably didn't want my pity.

1299
01:09:51,080 --> 01:09:54,279
- I definitely did!
- I just wanted to cheer him on.

1300
01:09:54,360 --> 01:09:56,840
Off was solid and consistent.

1301
01:09:56,920 --> 01:10:00,760
But Pancake was the winner in my eyes.

1302
01:10:01,480 --> 01:10:04,800
I've watched Pancake's journey
since Season 6.

1303
01:10:05,640 --> 01:10:10,320
And seeing her this time,
I just want to say thank you.

1304
01:10:10,400 --> 01:10:14,040
I stepped out of my comfort zone.
It's a huge relief, honestly.

1305
01:10:14,120 --> 01:10:17,920
Charin, what does
today's winning team receive?

1306
01:10:18,000 --> 01:10:19,920
Today's winning team

1307
01:10:20,000 --> 01:10:24,080
will be featured on Toyota
Digital Billboards across Bangkok.

1308
01:10:25,360 --> 01:10:26,520
Awesome. Okay.

1309
01:10:27,120 --> 01:10:28,320
Fantastic!

1310
01:10:28,400 --> 01:10:31,400
And now, it's time
to announce the results.

1311
01:10:31,480 --> 01:10:36,760
Charin, which team won
Drive the Runway campaign?

1312
01:10:45,280 --> 01:10:47,520
The winner of today's campaign is

1313
01:10:47,600 --> 01:10:49,040
Mentor Off's team.

1314
01:10:51,360 --> 01:10:52,960
Thank you.

1315
01:10:53,040 --> 01:10:55,880
We gave the client exactly
what they wanted today.

1316
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:58,200
I think that's what secured our win.

1317
01:11:28,200 --> 01:11:31,600
And for today,
a big thank you to our judges

1318
01:11:31,680 --> 01:11:34,080
for joining us to judge today's campaign.

1319
01:11:34,160 --> 01:11:37,960
Also, a special thanks
to Royal Mom and Tim…

1320
01:11:38,040 --> 01:11:40,760
for helping direct
our fashion video today.

1321
01:11:40,840 --> 01:11:44,280
- Thank you. Thank you so much.
- Glad to participate, thank you.

1322
01:11:44,360 --> 01:11:48,200
And last but not least,
thank you to all three of our mentors.

1323
01:11:49,880 --> 01:11:50,720
Thank you.

1324
01:11:50,800 --> 01:11:54,040
The product was the main key. I admit it.

1325
01:11:54,120 --> 01:11:55,480
It's a graceful defeat.

1326
01:11:55,560 --> 01:11:56,840
I'm sick of eliminating.

1327
01:11:56,920 --> 01:11:59,480
But if you want someone gone,
whisper it to me.

1328
01:11:59,560 --> 01:12:01,480
His decision would be fair.

1329
01:12:01,560 --> 01:12:04,360
But I'm not sure
which soap opera he's into right now.

1330
01:12:04,440 --> 01:12:06,840
Whatever he just watched,
he'll reuse the script.

1331
01:12:06,920 --> 01:12:10,560
You can't trust anyone.
Not a single soul today.

1332
01:12:41,760 --> 01:12:43,840
Greetings, greetings, and greetings.

1333
01:12:43,920 --> 01:12:45,840
Sorry, I'm a bit late.

1334
01:12:45,920 --> 01:12:47,480
The vibe was tense. I was like,

1335
01:12:47,560 --> 01:12:50,200
"Oh, man, what's going on?"
I couldn't read the room.

1336
01:12:50,280 --> 01:12:52,120
Have a seat. Sit down.

1337
01:12:52,200 --> 01:12:53,960
I was trying to read your vibe.

1338
01:12:54,040 --> 01:12:55,520
- Take a guess.
- Analyze him.

1339
01:12:55,600 --> 01:12:56,880
- Still handsome.
- Handsome.

1340
01:12:56,960 --> 01:12:59,120
He must be in a good mood.
No Black Room today.

1341
01:12:59,200 --> 01:13:00,760
We lost, you a-hole.

1342
01:13:00,840 --> 01:13:03,360
Are you serious?
We did all that and still lost?

1343
01:13:03,960 --> 01:13:05,240
Man. We did so well.

1344
01:13:05,320 --> 01:13:07,880
Was there really
another team better than us?

1345
01:13:08,400 --> 01:13:10,440
The situation was incredibly stressful.

1346
01:13:10,520 --> 01:13:13,560
Let's start with the opening.
What did you say? "Let's go, baby"?

1347
01:13:13,640 --> 01:13:17,320
Calling the cars "baby,"
it just didn't work.

1348
01:13:17,400 --> 01:13:19,560
He pointed out flaws,
and they were spot on.

1349
01:13:19,640 --> 01:13:21,240
We might have actually lost.

1350
01:13:21,320 --> 01:13:22,320
Moving on to Rome.

1351
01:13:22,400 --> 01:13:24,400
You stressed out again. Your face…

1352
01:13:24,480 --> 01:13:25,480
- It showed.
- Yes.

1353
01:13:26,520 --> 01:13:29,520
I don't know, I was just scared
of messing up the walk.

1354
01:13:29,600 --> 01:13:31,520
I thought then, "We probably lost."

1355
01:13:31,600 --> 01:13:35,920
But I didn't dare ask Off which team won.

1356
01:13:36,000 --> 01:13:38,680
I was afraid it would bring
everyone down even more.

1357
01:13:38,760 --> 01:13:41,280
Another thing, that final group pose.

1358
01:13:41,360 --> 01:13:43,800
You two did the exact same pose. Boom.

1359
01:13:43,880 --> 01:13:46,280
The exact same pose,
and I was like, "Oh, shit."

1360
01:13:46,360 --> 01:13:48,800
I told you to figure out an ending pose!

1361
01:13:48,880 --> 01:13:51,320
I completely tuned out
and stared at the floor.

1362
01:13:51,400 --> 01:13:52,400
Like I wasn't there.

1363
01:13:52,480 --> 01:13:53,440
I started thinking,

1364
01:13:53,520 --> 01:13:55,880
"What's the Black Room like?
What will I say?"

1365
01:13:55,960 --> 01:13:57,120
Who should I pick?

1366
01:13:58,160 --> 01:13:59,760
I don't know who to pick either.

1367
01:13:59,840 --> 01:14:02,320
It's stressful. Really?
We did so well in the end.

1368
01:14:02,400 --> 01:14:05,760
Do we really have to send
someone to the Black Room?

1369
01:14:09,200 --> 01:14:10,240
You seem so chill.

1370
01:14:11,840 --> 01:14:16,080
- Hello.
- Hello.

1371
01:14:16,880 --> 01:14:18,360
Today?

1372
01:14:18,440 --> 01:14:22,800
I tried to look like I was having fun,
but deep down I was worried.

1373
01:14:22,880 --> 01:14:26,040
Let me get straight to the point. Sorry.
The thing is…

1374
01:14:27,320 --> 01:14:28,640
We didn't win.

1375
01:14:29,680 --> 01:14:32,000
Just letting you know, we didn't win.

1376
01:14:32,080 --> 01:14:35,560
Ananda got straight to it.
Sharp and direct.

1377
01:14:35,640 --> 01:14:39,400
From what I heard,
our show was the most complete.

1378
01:14:39,480 --> 01:14:41,000
The best, show-wise.

1379
01:14:41,080 --> 01:14:45,120
But our mistakes were on
the client's technical side.

1380
01:14:45,200 --> 01:14:46,240
The car's functions.

1381
01:14:46,320 --> 01:14:50,840
The first flaw was the screen
in Donut's car, right?

1382
01:14:51,360 --> 01:14:52,680
And Lincoln's part.

1383
01:14:52,760 --> 01:14:55,600
The timing of opening the trunk
didn't sync with the camera.

1384
01:14:55,680 --> 01:14:59,080
But we have to accept it.
A mistake is a mistake, okay?

1385
01:14:59,160 --> 01:15:02,040
Call it bad luck. Call it whatever.

1386
01:15:02,120 --> 01:15:05,440
But we can't make excuses.
We just have to accept it.

1387
01:15:05,520 --> 01:15:09,760
Even if we couldn't fully control
everything.

1388
01:15:09,840 --> 01:15:11,840
Missing the brief was the biggest issue.

1389
01:15:11,920 --> 01:15:14,360
Because we're here
to deliver on the brief.

1390
01:15:14,440 --> 01:15:16,480
And if we fail the brief, it's game over.

1391
01:15:16,560 --> 01:15:18,600
I don't know who Ananda will pick.

1392
01:15:18,680 --> 01:15:21,760
But if he picks me,
I might be speechless right now.

1393
01:15:22,320 --> 01:15:24,160
But when the time comes,

1394
01:15:24,240 --> 01:15:26,520
like a cornered dog,
I have to speak up and fight.

1395
01:15:29,280 --> 01:15:31,520
- Hey, how's it going?
- Hello.

1396
01:15:33,600 --> 01:15:36,320
I brought you guys some gifts.

1397
01:15:36,920 --> 01:15:38,280
Thank you.

1398
01:15:38,360 --> 01:15:40,720
I brought some snacks.

1399
01:15:40,800 --> 01:15:43,440
Is it good news or bad news today?

1400
01:15:43,520 --> 01:15:46,040
My heart was pounding so fast right then.

1401
01:15:46,120 --> 01:15:47,280
How are you feeling?

1402
01:15:47,360 --> 01:15:50,960
When things glitched,
I was like, "Oh, man, what do we do?"

1403
01:15:51,040 --> 01:15:55,760
But we all agreed that our opening
was incredibly strong.

1404
01:15:55,840 --> 01:16:00,680
I was slightly panicked,
but I didn't know how it looked on camera.

1405
01:16:11,720 --> 01:16:13,000
A little bit.

1406
01:16:39,240 --> 01:16:41,760
We want to win
just like everyone else. It hurts.

1407
01:16:41,840 --> 01:16:45,440
Because we have to send someone
to the Black Room again.

1408
01:17:06,600 --> 01:17:09,280
It sucks when we don't win, because…

1409
01:17:10,040 --> 01:17:12,560
I have to send someone to the Black Room.

1410
01:17:12,640 --> 01:17:18,080
I just want to protect everyone
as much as I can. That's how I feel.

1411
01:17:18,160 --> 01:17:19,880
Speaking of improvement,

1412
01:17:19,960 --> 01:17:22,600
I feel like our team
has improved the most.

1413
01:17:22,680 --> 01:17:25,720
And I loved the ending
where you guys celebrated together.

1414
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:28,560
It was such
a beautiful brotherhood moment.

1415
01:17:28,640 --> 01:17:31,160
That's why I don't want to lose anyone.

1416
01:17:31,880 --> 01:17:33,800
Which right now, I'm just acting.

1417
01:17:37,480 --> 01:17:38,440
Seriously?

1418
01:17:38,520 --> 01:17:39,680
- Wait, did we win?
- Yes.

1419
01:17:43,520 --> 01:17:46,200
We know we're good.
We were bound to win anyway.

1420
01:17:49,280 --> 01:17:50,280
I knew it!

1421
01:17:54,160 --> 01:17:56,600
I knew it. Because the energy that day…

1422
01:17:56,680 --> 01:18:00,560
The energy was amazing.
It had to be winning energy.

1423
01:18:00,640 --> 01:18:05,240
The winner's prize is getting featured
on digital billboards all over Bangkok.

1424
01:18:05,320 --> 01:18:06,480
- Oh, wow.
- It's enough.

1425
01:18:06,560 --> 01:18:09,160
- That's already amazing.
- More than enough.

1426
01:18:09,240 --> 01:18:10,440
A childhood dream.

1427
01:18:10,520 --> 01:18:14,720
I can't wait to see it while driving past
the billboards. I'll look for my photo.

1428
01:18:14,800 --> 01:18:16,720
Let's do what I feel is most fair.

1429
01:18:17,240 --> 01:18:19,800
I'm sending both of you, okay?

1430
01:18:20,720 --> 01:18:23,720
I think it's very fair.
Fair to both of them.

1431
01:18:24,360 --> 01:18:28,120
Because both of your performances
were neck and neck.

1432
01:18:28,640 --> 01:18:31,080
You both made mistakes, okay?

1433
01:18:31,160 --> 01:18:33,400
And neither of you
did better than the other.

1434
01:18:33,480 --> 01:18:34,920
So I'm not saving anyone.

1435
01:18:35,000 --> 01:18:36,240
I'm not going to…

1436
01:18:36,320 --> 01:18:39,400
Look, both of you made mistakes.
Just tiny ones.

1437
01:18:39,480 --> 01:18:42,680
But they were there.
You have to understand that.

1438
01:18:42,760 --> 01:18:47,360
Instead of saving one of you,
I'll be fair. You're both going in.

1439
01:18:47,440 --> 01:18:50,240
Then tell Off why you deserve to be here.

1440
01:18:50,320 --> 01:18:54,080
First, my advice is to admit that…

1441
01:18:54,160 --> 01:18:56,400
- I messed up.
- Mistakes were actually made.

1442
01:18:56,480 --> 01:18:58,960
A technical error
that we didn't mean to happen.

1443
01:18:59,040 --> 01:19:03,520
Things were out of our control. Next time,
we'll make sure it doesn't happen again.

1444
01:19:03,600 --> 01:19:05,800
I don't want to hear excuses like…

1445
01:19:05,880 --> 01:19:08,680
"Oh, if this didn't happen,
I wouldn't have…"

1446
01:19:11,360 --> 01:19:15,960
Then focus on what matters.
Why you deserve to stay.

1447
01:19:16,040 --> 01:19:17,480
I'm not afraid to go in.

1448
01:19:17,560 --> 01:19:19,840
But once I'm there,
I just hope I make it back.

1449
01:19:19,920 --> 01:19:22,920
But the chances
of returning are pretty slim.

1450
01:19:24,000 --> 01:19:25,920
Don't cry yet, or you'll make me cry.

1451
01:19:29,520 --> 01:19:32,040
I feel like it comes down
to the performance.

1452
01:19:32,120 --> 01:19:34,960
Since both of their works were so similar…

1453
01:19:35,040 --> 01:19:36,600
They both have to go.

1454
01:19:36,680 --> 01:19:39,520
Everyone did their part well.

1455
01:19:39,600 --> 01:19:41,520
But having to choose one of you…

1456
01:19:41,600 --> 01:19:42,680
It's really hard.

1457
01:19:44,080 --> 01:19:45,040
Ultimately…

1458
01:19:45,640 --> 01:19:47,040
Leo.

1459
01:19:47,120 --> 01:19:48,680
I picked Leo.

1460
01:19:48,760 --> 01:19:52,480
It might be a bit hard
to coach him on set.

1461
01:19:52,560 --> 01:19:54,480
Because we already have four people.

1462
01:19:54,560 --> 01:19:58,560
Especially with the language barrier,
trying to understand things. So it's Leo.

1463
01:20:01,400 --> 01:20:04,880
Personally, I'm not a super energetic guy.

1464
01:20:04,960 --> 01:20:07,480
I'm not that enthusiastic.

1465
01:20:07,560 --> 01:20:09,400
I just like being quiet in my corner.

1466
01:20:09,480 --> 01:20:14,400
But I don't know
if it's the nature of this show

1467
01:20:14,480 --> 01:20:17,560
that makes it so hard for me to be alone.

1468
01:20:17,640 --> 01:20:23,160
But I know this experience
will help me, my teammates,

1469
01:20:23,240 --> 01:20:24,920
and Mentor Mile too.

1470
01:20:25,000 --> 01:20:28,960
Everyone cared for me and helped me.
I felt it, so I tried harder.

1471
01:20:29,040 --> 01:20:31,960
But because I can't speak Thai…

1472
01:20:32,040 --> 01:20:35,600
And my English isn't perfect either,
I get even more confused.

1473
01:20:35,680 --> 01:20:42,320
And when the results
don't always turn out the way I want,

1474
01:20:42,400 --> 01:20:46,400
I feel even more lost in myself.

1475
01:20:46,480 --> 01:20:52,000
Even so, Mile always looked out for me.

1476
01:20:53,960 --> 01:20:56,920
I could see that he really cared.

1477
01:20:57,600 --> 01:20:59,560
I don't know what to say.

1478
01:20:59,640 --> 01:21:02,840
But what I want to say most right now is…

1479
01:21:02,920 --> 01:21:04,360
Joining this show,

1480
01:21:04,440 --> 01:21:11,080
I've felt so much connection, gratitude,
and love for everyone here.

1481
01:21:13,440 --> 01:21:16,080
More importantly,
these feelings will last a lifetime.

1482
01:21:16,160 --> 01:21:22,200
<i>Oppa </i>is the big brother of the house.
And everyone in the team adores him.

1483
01:21:22,280 --> 01:21:25,800
Be proud that everyone believes in you.

1484
01:21:53,000 --> 01:21:55,920
I think Mentor Off
might just be kind for once.

1485
01:21:56,000 --> 01:21:58,800
I have faith that Leo is going to fight.

1486
01:21:58,880 --> 01:22:00,360
And he'll do great.

1487
01:22:00,440 --> 01:22:02,880
Even if his Thai isn't perfect.

1488
01:22:02,960 --> 01:22:05,960
He'll fight to come back
because he loves us all.

1489
01:22:34,120 --> 01:22:35,400
Hello.

1490
01:22:37,400 --> 01:22:39,960
Pan and Ananda sent two of you?

1491
01:22:40,960 --> 01:22:43,760
They're playing games with me,
sending both of you.

1492
01:22:43,840 --> 01:22:45,320
Mile sent in a strong player.

1493
01:22:45,400 --> 01:22:47,800
They're definitely pushing me
to keep you all.

1494
01:22:47,880 --> 01:22:48,920
It's so obvious.

1495
01:22:49,000 --> 01:22:53,600
Look, this is the final Black Room.
Why would Ananda send two people?

1496
01:22:53,680 --> 01:22:55,000
What was his reason?

1497
01:22:55,080 --> 01:22:58,200
Because during yesterday's campaign,

1498
01:22:58,280 --> 01:23:01,280
the mistake was on both of us.

1499
01:23:01,360 --> 01:23:05,280
We were supposed to show the cars'
features, but the camera didn't catch it.

1500
01:23:06,440 --> 01:23:08,800
Everything else was perfect.

1501
01:23:08,880 --> 01:23:11,240
I'm sure you saw that too.

1502
01:23:11,320 --> 01:23:14,600
But the camera missed
the features the client wanted.

1503
01:23:14,680 --> 01:23:18,120
And it happened to us
because we were the ones using the cars.

1504
01:23:18,200 --> 01:23:22,600
So Ananda took the fairest route
and sent us both in.

1505
01:23:22,680 --> 01:23:25,720
Lincoln, tell me first.
Why did your team lose?

1506
01:23:25,800 --> 01:23:27,600
It was a technical issue.

1507
01:23:27,680 --> 01:23:31,920
I felt our teamwork was amazing.

1508
01:23:32,000 --> 01:23:34,400
I really thought we could win.

1509
01:23:34,480 --> 01:23:36,440
It was just a technicality.

1510
01:23:36,520 --> 01:23:40,440
Technicality? Then why didn't my team
have any technical errors?

1511
01:23:40,520 --> 01:23:41,840
Because…

1512
01:23:42,440 --> 01:23:47,040
We tried to do something a bit harder.

1513
01:23:47,120 --> 01:23:48,720
You think mine was easy?

1514
01:23:48,800 --> 01:23:50,840
No, I didn't mean yours was easy.

1515
01:23:50,920 --> 01:23:52,640
Just for our skill level.

1516
01:23:52,720 --> 01:23:56,200
But I just want to say
we really gave it our all.

1517
01:23:56,280 --> 01:23:57,800
I know. Everyone did great.

1518
01:23:57,880 --> 01:24:01,000
This last campaign
was the closest match yet.

1519
01:24:01,080 --> 01:24:03,120
But next week is the Final Walk.

1520
01:24:03,200 --> 01:24:07,000
If he sent you two here and kept Kimhan,
hasn't he already made up his mind?

1521
01:24:08,520 --> 01:24:10,240
What do you think?

1522
01:24:10,320 --> 01:24:12,200
- I don't think so.
- You don't think so?

1523
01:24:12,280 --> 01:24:14,160
So, why didn't he send all three?

1524
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:18,680
It was a technical issue.
It wasn't your fault, was it?

1525
01:24:18,760 --> 01:24:20,120
Right, a technical issue.

1526
01:24:20,200 --> 01:24:22,320
Right, a technical issue for both of you.

1527
01:24:22,400 --> 01:24:23,440
- Yes.
- Yes.

1528
01:24:23,520 --> 01:24:24,840
Why not send all three?

1529
01:24:24,920 --> 01:24:26,960
He judged based on the performance.

1530
01:24:27,040 --> 01:24:31,560
Because the technical errors happened
specifically with my car and Lincoln's.

1531
01:24:32,200 --> 01:24:34,920
Kimhan couldn't drive
and didn't use the car.

1532
01:24:35,000 --> 01:24:37,280
He executed everything
much smoother than us.

1533
01:24:37,360 --> 01:24:40,560
That's why he chose
to send the two of us here.

1534
01:24:40,640 --> 01:24:42,040
I get the technical errors.

1535
01:24:42,120 --> 01:24:43,480
But when mistakes happen,

1536
01:24:43,560 --> 01:24:45,320
you have to blame yourself first.

1537
01:24:45,400 --> 01:24:46,600
That mindset is wrong.

1538
01:24:46,680 --> 01:24:49,320
Why couldn't you
solve the problem on the spot?

1539
01:24:49,400 --> 01:24:50,880
Sending two people in.

1540
01:24:50,960 --> 01:24:52,680
I wouldn't do it. It's too risky.

1541
01:24:52,760 --> 01:24:54,880
I'm not trying to blame anyone.

1542
01:24:54,960 --> 01:24:58,160
I just feel like he has low-key
already made up his mind.

1543
01:25:00,320 --> 01:25:02,040
Let me talk to Leo.

1544
01:25:02,120 --> 01:25:04,720
I want to know why Mile sent you.

1545
01:25:04,800 --> 01:25:09,200
I think Mile gave me a major role
in this campaign.

1546
01:25:09,280 --> 01:25:13,600
So I fully committed
and poured everything into it.

1547
01:25:13,680 --> 01:25:15,760
But ultimately, our team lost.

1548
01:25:15,840 --> 01:25:19,800
Therefore, I have to take responsibility
for that failure.

1549
01:25:19,880 --> 01:25:23,960
But from what I saw yesterday,
you weren't the worst performer, Leo.

1550
01:25:24,040 --> 01:25:25,520
I honestly can't say

1551
01:25:25,600 --> 01:25:30,040
whether I did the best or the worst,
now that I'm standing in the Black Room…

1552
01:25:30,120 --> 01:25:32,840
It doesn't even matter anymore.

1553
01:25:32,920 --> 01:25:36,000
Does the language barrier
affect your work?

1554
01:25:36,080 --> 01:25:40,760
Even though it gets frustrating
not being able to speak Thai well myself,

1555
01:25:40,840 --> 01:25:43,600
I want to say that
in the master classes and campaigns,

1556
01:25:43,680 --> 01:25:46,480
I don't think language
was an obstacle for me at all.

1557
01:25:47,080 --> 01:25:50,400
I will try my absolute best with my Thai.

1558
01:25:51,480 --> 01:25:53,280
And I…

1559
01:25:55,560 --> 01:25:59,400
I am practicing my Thai
as much as I can right now.

1560
01:26:00,040 --> 01:26:02,080
You might need to practice a little more.

1561
01:26:02,160 --> 01:26:03,400
Yes.

1562
01:26:03,920 --> 01:26:08,080
At the end of the day, I just feel like
if mentors can send you into this room,

1563
01:26:08,160 --> 01:26:11,680
it means they have their eyes set
on someone for the Final Walk.

1564
01:26:11,760 --> 01:26:14,120
If not this week,
you'll get heartbroken next week.

1565
01:26:14,200 --> 01:26:16,440
If not today, then tomorrow.

1566
01:26:16,520 --> 01:26:19,200
It's not like that.
There's still one more task left.

1567
01:26:19,280 --> 01:26:23,800
I don't think my mentors have decided.
They may want to judge the next challenge.

1568
01:26:23,880 --> 01:26:25,240
Are you sure?

1569
01:26:25,320 --> 01:26:28,800
But what if you get back
and the Final Walk goes to Kimhan?

1570
01:26:28,880 --> 01:26:31,720
I don't want your mentors to hurt you.
I can do it myself.

1571
01:26:31,800 --> 01:26:34,800
That way, you won't resent them.
Resenting me is better.

1572
01:26:34,880 --> 01:26:38,520
Even if Mile already has
a Final Walk pick in mind…

1573
01:26:38,600 --> 01:26:42,080
And even if that person isn't me,
there's still time…

1574
01:26:42,160 --> 01:26:44,680
Plenty of time to change a person's mind.

1575
01:26:44,760 --> 01:26:47,480
Therefore, I deserve the chance to stay.

1576
01:26:47,560 --> 01:26:50,880
I understand
this is a competition for all of us.

1577
01:26:51,480 --> 01:26:55,960
But I believe
I still have the potential to improve.

1578
01:26:56,040 --> 01:26:57,760
Ananda didn't save my boy.

1579
01:26:58,360 --> 01:27:00,120
Pan didn't save my boy either.

1580
01:27:01,360 --> 01:27:02,320
You remember that?

1581
01:27:02,400 --> 01:27:04,880
I really started from zero, you know that.

1582
01:27:04,960 --> 01:27:07,680
I've been steadily improving step by step.

1583
01:27:07,760 --> 01:27:09,480
I never get tired, never give up.

1584
01:27:09,560 --> 01:27:12,200
I'm always ready to learn new things.

1585
01:27:12,280 --> 01:27:14,920
The game is almost over.

1586
01:27:15,000 --> 01:27:16,680
This is the final stretch.

1587
01:27:17,480 --> 01:27:18,840
Please, give me the chance.

1588
01:27:18,920 --> 01:27:21,760
I really love you guys,
but this is a game.

1589
01:27:28,280 --> 01:27:31,720
Both Lincoln and Donut…

1590
01:27:32,960 --> 01:27:34,440
Neither of you is The Face.

1591
01:27:36,760 --> 01:27:37,920
I'm sorry.

1592
01:27:38,000 --> 01:27:39,200
It's okay, I understand.

1593
01:27:39,280 --> 01:27:41,000
- I'm so sorry.
- I understand.

1594
01:27:42,440 --> 01:27:43,280
Leo.

1595
01:27:44,840 --> 01:27:46,360
You're not The Face either.

1596
01:27:50,840 --> 01:27:52,160
I'm sorry.

1597
01:27:52,240 --> 01:27:53,160
That's okay.

1598
01:27:55,960 --> 01:28:00,800
When I first met Mile,
I felt that if I was chosen

1599
01:28:00,880 --> 01:28:02,160
or got to pick my mentor,

1600
01:28:02,240 --> 01:28:04,720
it was always going to be Mile.

1601
01:28:04,800 --> 01:28:07,160
I wanted us
to reach the Final Walk together.

1602
01:28:07,240 --> 01:28:09,080
But now, I have to leave the show.

1603
01:28:09,160 --> 01:28:13,880
I'm still so grateful he took care of me.
Thank you so much.

1604
01:28:15,600 --> 01:28:20,640
I don't feel bad. I'm just grateful
to have made it to week six.

1605
01:28:20,720 --> 01:28:24,440
I never thought I would survive this long.

1606
01:28:24,520 --> 01:28:28,280
And I'm glad I got to know
Mentor Ananda and Mentor Pancake.

1607
01:28:28,360 --> 01:28:30,240
They were so kind to me.

1608
01:28:31,120 --> 01:28:32,400
Am I sad? Yes, I am.

1609
01:28:32,480 --> 01:28:35,680
Whatever caused the mistakes
that happened,

1610
01:28:35,760 --> 01:28:38,640
I can't blame anyone else. It's on me.

1611
01:28:38,720 --> 01:28:42,240
I just want to tell Kimhan
that I believe in him.

1612
01:28:42,320 --> 01:28:46,160
He can bring home the win for Team Panda.

1613
01:28:46,240 --> 01:28:47,720
I believe in his potential.

1614
01:28:47,800 --> 01:28:50,720
Keep fighting. You've got this.

1615
01:28:54,520 --> 01:28:55,720
He brought a suitcase.

1616
01:28:55,800 --> 01:28:58,840
Is that his elimination room outfit?

1617
01:28:58,920 --> 01:29:01,520
He looks badass. Has a suitcase with him.

1618
01:29:01,600 --> 01:29:03,920
I'm not buying any insurance. Not buying.

1619
01:29:04,000 --> 01:29:06,480
And the survivor… is in here.

1620
01:29:07,440 --> 01:29:10,080
First off,
if that's a Dior bag, I'm opening it.

1621
01:29:10,160 --> 01:29:11,320
What's his game here?

1622
01:29:14,720 --> 01:29:18,040
No one. They're all gone.

1623
01:29:18,800 --> 01:29:21,600
Nobody. I eliminated them all.

1624
01:29:22,400 --> 01:29:24,720
You eliminated all three, Off?

1625
01:29:24,800 --> 01:29:26,720
I thought he was joking at first.

1626
01:29:26,800 --> 01:29:29,240
Deep down, I kept hoping
Donut would walk back in.

1627
01:29:29,320 --> 01:29:31,280
- Did you really mean it?
- Really?

1628
01:29:31,880 --> 01:29:32,760
I mean it.

1629
01:29:33,320 --> 01:29:35,360
Yesterday, you said you won't eliminate.

1630
01:29:35,440 --> 01:29:37,680
That was yesterday.

1631
01:29:37,760 --> 01:29:39,520
This is today.

1632
01:29:39,600 --> 01:29:42,440
Now, I believe it.
There really is no honor among thieves.

1633
01:29:42,520 --> 01:29:45,440
Hold on. Seriously?
You eliminated everyone?

1634
01:29:45,520 --> 01:29:46,960
- They're gone.
- Damn.

1635
01:29:47,800 --> 01:29:49,000
I'm being serious, Mile.

1636
01:29:49,080 --> 01:29:50,480
Is this your final decision?

1637
01:29:50,560 --> 01:29:52,680
I was in shock. What a massive plot twist.

1638
01:29:52,760 --> 01:29:53,840
All in one go?

1639
01:29:53,920 --> 01:29:56,400
That's it. My mind is made up.
No second-guessing.

1640
01:29:56,480 --> 01:30:00,240
Sent in three, eliminated all three.
It's all for my own boys.

1641
01:30:00,840 --> 01:30:03,600
Honestly, I feel like this is bullsh--

1642
01:30:03,680 --> 01:30:04,960
I'm not cursing at Off.

1643
01:30:05,040 --> 01:30:07,200
- Who didn't fight for it?
- None of them did.

1644
01:30:07,280 --> 01:30:10,720
Are you clenching your fists, Mile?
Mile, it's all just a game.

1645
01:30:10,800 --> 01:30:13,520
Outside of this, we're still friends.

1646
01:30:13,600 --> 01:30:15,760
I'm not mad. I'm not mad at all.

1647
01:30:15,840 --> 01:30:17,640
But since when were we even friends?

1648
01:30:17,720 --> 01:30:21,880
Who do you see in the Final Walk?
If it's Leo, you shouldn't have sent him.

1649
01:30:21,960 --> 01:30:25,040
I don't know what Mile was thinking.
Sure, Leo messed up.

1650
01:30:25,120 --> 01:30:27,240
But he probably wasn't the weakest link.

1651
01:30:27,320 --> 01:30:28,840
I love all my guys.

1652
01:30:28,920 --> 01:30:31,480
If I could just send the weakest link,

1653
01:30:31,560 --> 01:30:33,880
I would've sent the driver in.

1654
01:30:33,960 --> 01:30:36,880
Are you saying
Leo didn't fight for his spot?

1655
01:30:36,960 --> 01:30:39,080
- He fought. Just not hard enough.
- I see.

1656
01:30:39,160 --> 01:30:42,840
This is pure gameplay.
Off's totally playing the game.

1657
01:30:42,920 --> 01:30:43,840
I get it.

1658
01:30:43,920 --> 01:30:46,560
- If he fought harder, I would've kept him.
- I get it.

1659
01:30:46,640 --> 01:30:48,080
Honestly, I'm a fair guy.

1660
01:30:48,160 --> 01:30:50,680
But if it were me, I would never send Leo.

1661
01:30:50,760 --> 01:30:54,120
I'm playing the game too.
I wouldn't make a stupid move like that.

1662
01:30:54,200 --> 01:30:57,600
No way.
I don't believe my boys didn't fight.

1663
01:30:57,680 --> 01:31:00,720
I asked him,
"Where do you think you went wrong?"

1664
01:31:00,800 --> 01:31:01,720
"Technical issue."

1665
01:31:01,800 --> 01:31:04,840
First rule,
if you lose, you blame yourself.

1666
01:31:04,920 --> 01:31:07,000
- Donut…
- Donut blamed technical issues too.

1667
01:31:07,080 --> 01:31:08,560
Really? Are you serious?

1668
01:31:08,640 --> 01:31:10,600
Donut would never say that.

1669
01:31:10,680 --> 01:31:13,640
Do you believe this?
We were very clear about this.

1670
01:31:13,720 --> 01:31:14,720
Go check the tape.

1671
01:31:14,800 --> 01:31:17,080
I think Ananda must be furious right now.

1672
01:31:17,160 --> 01:31:19,760
Every time I stand here and speak,
it's the truth.

1673
01:31:19,840 --> 01:31:21,960
I don't joke around on this show.

1674
01:31:22,040 --> 01:31:25,720
He still doesn't believe that Donut
blamed the technical issues.

1675
01:31:25,800 --> 01:31:28,800
When we spoke privately in the room,
he kept blaming himself.

1676
01:31:28,880 --> 01:31:30,240
- I see.
- Yes.

1677
01:31:30,320 --> 01:31:34,240
Deep down,
I know he wouldn't make excuses.

1678
01:31:34,320 --> 01:31:36,960
If someone actually took the blame,

1679
01:31:37,040 --> 01:31:38,880
I would keep him right here.

1680
01:31:38,960 --> 01:31:42,280
That's just cruel. Don't you have a heart?

1681
01:31:42,360 --> 01:31:43,880
Seriously, I love the kid.

1682
01:31:43,960 --> 01:31:46,240
No, you don't.

1683
01:31:46,320 --> 01:31:48,800
If you did, you would give him a chance.

1684
01:31:49,960 --> 01:31:50,960
Let's go home.

1685
01:31:51,760 --> 01:31:55,960
What he did today wasn't a strategy.
It's just who he is.

1686
01:31:56,040 --> 01:31:59,120
I'd say worse, but they'd bleep it out.
Let's leave it at that.

1687
01:31:59,200 --> 01:32:01,520
Mile is the hero. I'm the villain.

1688
01:32:01,600 --> 01:32:03,680
Whatever he calls me, I'm the bad guy.

1689
01:32:03,760 --> 01:32:06,200
If I clap back, I'm still the bad guy.

1690
01:32:06,280 --> 01:32:08,320
I get hate from him and his fans.

1691
01:32:09,640 --> 01:32:13,360
- You okay? You'll do this for Donut?
- I want to do it for Donut.

1692
01:32:13,440 --> 01:32:16,640
Let me propose this. Let's be fair.

1693
01:32:16,720 --> 01:32:19,720
If Kimhan wins the next campaign,
I want this, okay?

1694
01:32:19,800 --> 01:32:22,120
The next prize is two Final Walk spots.

1695
01:32:22,200 --> 01:32:24,320
But how is that fair if I win?

1696
01:32:24,400 --> 01:32:27,240
So there must be
two Final Walk spots for my team.

1697
01:32:27,320 --> 01:32:29,320
I'm giving Donut a chance.

1698
01:32:29,400 --> 01:32:30,920
At least let him come back.

1699
01:32:31,000 --> 01:32:33,520
I want to fight for someone.

1700
01:32:33,600 --> 01:32:35,840
And that someone is Donut.

1701
01:32:35,920 --> 01:32:40,280
Huge congrats to our first
Final Walk team, Team Panda.

1702
01:32:40,880 --> 01:32:42,280
I'm so happy for them.

1703
01:32:43,680 --> 01:32:45,880
I must have jumped more than ten times.

1704
01:32:46,480 --> 01:32:49,080
Today, I just have
to grit my teeth and fight.

1705
01:32:49,160 --> 01:32:52,280
I've never seen Kimhan this stressed.

1706
01:32:52,360 --> 01:32:54,960
But you have so many guys.
It's a waste of time.

1707
01:32:55,040 --> 01:32:56,840
- Who's next?
- You're up!

1708
01:32:59,320 --> 01:33:02,560
This is a once-in-a-lifetime shot.
I have to take it.

1709
01:33:02,640 --> 01:33:04,000
Here's some lucky money.

1710
01:33:04,080 --> 01:33:05,000
A bribe?

1711
01:33:05,080 --> 01:33:07,680
This is an incentive. This is a bribe.

1712
01:33:07,760 --> 01:33:09,200
Go! Good job!

1713
01:33:09,280 --> 01:33:10,560
Give it everything!

